## Exporting graphics

### Our options

- 'Export' button in RStudio
- Graphical devices
- `ggsave()`  (ensure ragg is installed for nicer images)
- Formats: png, jpg, pdf, etc.

## Exporting

:::{.callout-note}
## 
We can asign plots to workspace objects
:::


::: {.cell hash='visualization_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-13_a8398540e80efd3bd45bd75d90c7fb27'}

```{.r .cell-code}
my_plot <- 
ggplot(penguins,
       aes(x=bill_length_mm,
          y=flipper_length_mm))+
  geom_point(size=2,pch=21)

ggsave(my_plot, 
  filename = "myplotgs.png",
    width = 10, 
    height = 10,
    units ="cm",
    dpi = 200)
```
:::



