## Composing plots with `patchwork`

::: columns
::: {.column width="20%"}
![](imgs/patchworklogo.png)
:::

::: {.column width="80%"}
-  `+` to combine plots
-  `|` side by side
-  `/` above/below 
:::
:::   

Simple algebra for arranging and nesting elements

- `plot_layout()` controls composition
- `plot_annotation()` tag elements or add labels to composite plot


##


::: {.cell hash='visualization_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-16_a27bddfae408e64d5e9b35440231902d'}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(openintro)
data("fastfood")
ggplot(fastfood,aes(calories,sodium))+
     geom_point()+
ggplot(fastfood,aes(restaurant,sodium))+
     geom_jitter(aes(color=restaurant))+
     theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90),
           legend.position = "none")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](visualization_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-16-1.png){width=2000}
:::
:::


------

Easier to read:


::: {.cell hash='visualization_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-17_ea3fff761e6a8ad1c45e9772079f4186'}

```{.r .cell-code}
cal_sodium_plt <- ggplot(fastfood,aes(calories,sodium))+
     geom_point()
rest_sodium_plt <- ggplot(fastfood,aes(restaurant,sodium))+
     geom_jitter(aes(color=restaurant))+
     theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90),
           legend.position = "none")

cal_sodium_plt+rest_sodium_plt
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](visualization_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-17-1.png){width=2000}
:::
:::


