## Formatting text

We can use _markdown_ syntax to format text in different elements of our plots. Enable formatting with `element_markdown()` from the **`ggtext`** package.

[ggtext documentation](https://wilkelab.org/ggtext/)


##


::: {.cell hash='visualization_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-24_50532d49d8d01a563dddfef0317417ff'}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(ggtext)

fastfood %>% mutate(Fats=sat_fat>15) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(total_fat,sat_fat,color=Fats))+
geom_point()+
  scale_color_discrete(labels=c("**Greasy** junk" ,"Low fat"))+
  theme(legend.text = element_markdown())
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](visualization_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-24-1.png){width=2000}
:::
:::



